    <p>GEIGER: I think inside I secretly did a little happy dance, you know. I hate seeing the building deteriorate. So I'm really glad that somebody is going to move in and take care of it. I thought they were going to bulldoze it.</p>
    <p>WALLACE: She can just see the shiny new windshields rolling out of Fuyao, shipped off to assembly lines for Honda, Kia and, who else, General Motors.</p>
